      • getTimestamp

        public long getTimestamp()
        Gets the timestamp of a CLE2 layer. For layers on remote CLE2 service, this indicates time of last modification of any data contained within the layer. For layers stored locally, this is a timestamp of a CLE2 layer as it was at the time it was downloaded from remote CLE2 service. Layers that were created and stored locally do not have a timestamp.
        Returns:
        a timestamp - number of milliseconds since Unix epoch or 0 for layers that did not originate from remote CLE2 service
